		<description><![CDATA[You can now vent your frustrations with tech startups inside Counter-Strike: Global Offensive. A new map, Breach, sends us to fight through a startup office which even has a slide in the lobby. Of course they have a slide. That&#8217;s just how fun and anti-establishment they are. Not that we&#8217;re allowed to ride the slide [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://assets.rockpapershotgun.com/images/2019/08/counter-strike-global-offensive-breach.jpg"><img src="https://assets.rockpapershotgun.com/images/2019/08/counter-strike-global-offensive-breach.jpg/RPSS/resize/690x-1/format/jpg//RPSS/resize/670x-1/format/jpg/" width="670" /></a></p>
<p>You can now vent your frustrations with tech startups inside <a href="https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/game/counter-strike-global-offensive">Counter-Strike: Global Offensive</a>. A new map, Breach, sends us to fight through a startup office which even has a slide in the lobby. Of course they have a slide. That&#8217;s just how fun and anti-establishment they are. Not that we&#8217;re allowed to ride the slide in-game. Yesterday&#8217;s update also brought back Seaside, a map removed a few years back, and has reworked areas of Vertigo. After all, man cannot live on Dust alone &#8211; no matter what <a href="https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2019/07/18/dustnet-is-a-strange-and-wonderful-dream-of-the-last-de_dust2-server/">Dustnet&#8217;s fascinating futureworld suggests</a>.</p>
